The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter Police in Bulawayo have arrested two suspects who committed a spate of robberies in the city. The two allegedly sprayed their victims with an itchy substance on the eyes before robbing them. The suspects, a male aged 22 and his female accomplice aged 29, were driving around the city in a Honda Fit vehicle targeting their prey. “The suspects sprayed their victims with an unknown itchy substance on the eyes making them unable to see and, in the process, stole their property,” said the police on their Twitter page. “They would also target unsuspecting cell phone operators, snatch their cell phones and flee in the get-away vehicle.” The police said further investigations were still in progress.